Essay #1: Gender applied to Frankenstein:  
How does Frankenstein fit into feminist discourse of the time? 
This is a really interesting question considering her parents were two of the most well-known feminists of their time. It is fascinating to see how, although she never met her, how much Wollstonecraft influenced her daughter’s work.
Interview a Classics professor (Dr. Richard Turner is who I intend on asking)—ask about their take on feminism within Frankenstein and how that compares to other works written by women that were known feminists of the same time. 
